BriefingText: On early Gemini flights, astronauts manually controlled much of the spacecraft's maneuvers during re-entry. Just before re-entry, the Gemini capsule would jettison the retrograde section, leaving only the cone-shaped spacecraft holding the crew. In most cases, the astronauts used the capsule's controls to maneuver it so that the large, blunt end faced the Earth. The friction generated from the spacecraft moving through the atmosphere at tremendous speeds produced intense heat. Without the heat shield on the base of the Gemini spacecraft, the astronauts inside the capsule wouldn't have been able to survive. Finally the Gemini Spacecraft lands safely in the Atlantic Ocean.
Description: In this Tutorial we will teach how to perform the Deorbit-Reentry-Landing procedure which is a requirement for every Gemini Program mission.

MissionCommands.Message: Good morning {{profileName}}, I am Hector and I will be your astronaut instructor.
In this Tutorial I will teach you how to perform the Deorbit-Reentry-Landing procedure for the Gemini Spacecraft.

Atmospheric entry or re-entry is the movement of an object from outer space into and through the gases of an atmosphere surrounding some planets. This procedure allows a controlled atmospheric entry, descent and landing of spacecraft on Earth.
Atmospheric Drag and Aerodynamic Heating can cause an atmospheric breakup capable of completely disintegrating any spacecraft, that's why it is so important to master this procedure.
Just before re-entry, the Gemini capsule will jettison the Retrograde section, leaving only the cone-shaped spacecraft holding the crew.

The Tip/Nose of the Gemini capsule contains a parachute system. Small explosives will deploy the parachutes to slow the capsule's descent. The capsule will shortly after make a big splash in the ocean and float until a rescue ship retrieves the vehicle and astronauts.
Let's get started. We are currently 80 minutes from start the re-entry.
Well, let's start this lesson by learning the Gemini Spacecraft Deorbit-Reentry-Landing Procedure.

First, we need to Set the Gemini spacecraft to Retrograde attitude, for this: Hit 'V' on your keyboard for opening [V]IEW SELECTOR, then Select [CENTER PEDESTAL]. In the [PROP MOTOR VALVES] section set [OAMS] TO = > [OPEN].
Now, in [CNTL PWR] section set [OAMS] TO = > [ON].
This [OAMS] are needed for performing the Retro Burn.
Make sure that [ATTITUDE CONTROL] is set to [PLAT] [CENTER PEDESTAL].
This will Hold the Gemini Spacecraft Attitude to the PLATFORM Selected.
Then, set [PLATFORM] TO => [BEF] [CENTER PEDESTAL].
Now the Gemini spacecraft should be changing its attitude to retrograde, look at the [FDAI] Ball.

Again, hit 'V' on your keyboard for opening [V]IEW SELECTOR, then select [CENTER PEDESTAL]. Set [COMPUTER] TO => [RE ENT] wait for 10 minutes for the OBC memory to erase and LOAD the reentry program (or time skip until 10 minutes has passed, or use the event timer}.

10 minutes has Passed, Press Computer [START] button NOW! (will bright Green). (If it does not turn Green, you need to wait for the 10 Minutes, the AUX TAPE light will illuminate green when it's loading, do not proceed with this tutorial until this is completed).

Now, let's check how much time we have left for Retro Burn. Once again Hit 'V' on your keyboard for opening [V]IEW SELECTOR, then Select [PILOT'S PANEL]. go to OBC Computer Terminal: press [1] on the MDIU.
Next press [9] on the MDIU.
And Finally Press [READ OUT].
The new reading will show time for Retro burn in Seconds.

Now, we will configure the Event Timer counting down for [10:00] minutes (DN mode), Hit 'V' on your keyboard for opening [V]IEW SELECTOR, then Select [COMMANDER PANEL]. Then turn the Event Timer Dial counterclockwise (Left) to increase numbers until getting to [10:00] minutes.
Once [10:00] is Displayed, turn Dial clockwise back to middle position [0]. Next, turn [LEFT PIN] DOWN TO => [STOP].
And finally, turn [RIGHT PIN] Down TO => [DN].
For now on you better keep an eye on CORE 19 on the Gemini OBC Computer Terminal, wait until it displays [600] Seconds. You need to press [READ OUT] every time you want to update the display.
You may use Time Skipping here if you wish, but keep in mind that when we are just 600 Seconds away from Retro burn, we must start our counting down.
When [600] is displayed, Press that Pin up! Turn Event Timer [LEFT PIN] UP TO => [STBY].
Now the Event Timer Counting Down has Started!

Now, Hit 'V' on your Computer Keyboard, then in [V]IEW SELECTOR hit [MISSION PAD] and then, select [5 MIN TO RETRO Checklist] Finally press run, but do not excecute the Checklist yet, (do not press any button until the time is right).

When counting down gets to [5:00], start executing the [5 MIN TO RETRO Checklist]. Pay attention to the Checklist Indicator (Blue Guidance Box) it should be hovering over the proper PIN/BUTTON/SWITCH/KNOB you must press.
Follow every PIN/BUTTON/SWITCH/KNOB pressing instructions from the Checklist.
Pay close attention to Sequencers [CENTER PANEL] (this is the key), once the first Sequencer lights up (bright yellow}) you press it, [IND RETRO ATT] will be the first.
Look, at the [SEQUENCERS] soon they will start Flashing.
When [SEQUENCERS] Start Flashing Press them begining with [IND RETRO ATT] (First One Frorm Top to Down).
CONTINUE PRESSING from Top to Down, then when Sequencer [BTRY PWR] lights up, now you need to press some battery switches, change the view  to [V]IEW [PILOT's SEAT].
Then, continue pressing the rest of the Sequencers in the same order (Notice that once a Sequencer is pressed, it turns green).
After pressing every Sequencer buttons, Hit 'V' on your Computer Keyboard, then in [V]IEW SELECTOR hit [MISSION PAD] and then, select [30 SEC TO RETRO] Checklist and press run.
Do not execute anything yet, just wait for the Event timer count down to show 30 seconds left. Once 30 seconds is displayed, Execute the [30 SEC TO RETRO] checklist.
If you followed every step correctly, you have already pressed [ARM AUTO RETRO] Sequencer, soon you will be Burning in Retrograde.
Wait for the Burn!
Finally, Wait for [JETT RETRO] Sequencer to light up. Then, After hitting [JETT Retro] sequencer, you are ready to run [POST RETRO JETTISON] Checklist.
Go to [V]IEW SELECTOR, hit [MISSION PAD] then, [CHECKLISTS] and fnally select [POST RETRO JETTISON] Checklist and press Run. Execute the [POST RETRO JETTISON] Checklist now!
Once finished the whole checklist, go to [V]IEW SELECTOR hit [COMMANDER'S PANEL], Now set FDAI reading to => [COMP].
Then, set FDAI reading to => [ATT].
Make sure [COMPUTER] is SET TO => [RE ENT] mode and turned on [bright Green light].
Next, in [V]IEW SELECTOR, hit [CENTER PEDESTAL]. Now, set [ATTITUDE CONTROL] TO => [RATE CMD (RE-ENT)].
Finally set [PLATFORM] TO => [FREE].
Now go to [V]IEW SELECTOR, then hit [COMMANDER'S PANEL], Next Zoom in the [FDAI] Ball so you can see it Clearly.
Now your pilot's skills will be proven!

Change the Gemini Spacecraft Attitude manually, so those needles point to the Center, it is done by changing the (ROLL, PITCH and YAW attitudes) these are measured in degrees, Hit Roger for further Instructions.
Remember the Following Keyboard keys: [W: PITCH DOWN], [S: PITCH UP], [A: YAW LEFT], [D: YAW RIGHT], [Q: ROLL LEFT], [E: ROLL RIGHT].
Keep those Needles Centerd as much you can, you may use Time Skipping if you wish, notice that Time Skipping is not available when the entry interface is starting.

Wait for for the reentry procedure to end before continuing this tutorial. During reentry, your spacecraft will shake as it gets struck by the atmosphere, burning depicted as a bright yellow light wrapping around the capsule. Do not anything while performing reentry except monitoring and checking attitude.
Once everything is calm again, it means you already performed the Reentry successfully. Now you can continue this Tutorial, you may Hit Roger.
Now go to [V]IEW SELECTOR, then hit [COMMANDER'S PANEL]. Next take a look at the [40K] and [10.6K] indicators.
When [40K] indicator lights up [COMMANDER'S PANEL], go to [V]IEW SELECTOR, hit [CENTER PEDESTAL], then press [HI ALT DROGUE]. This will Deploy the Altitude Drogue.
Press [HI ALT DROGUE] NOW! [CENTER PEDESTAL]
Then, when [10.6K] indicator lights up [COMMANDER'S PANEL], go to [V]IEW SELECTOR, hit [CENTER PEDESTAL] and press [PARA]. This will Deploy the Parachute.
Press [PARA] NOW! [CENTER PEDESTAL]

Again go to [V]IEW SELECTOR, then hit [COMMANDER'S PANEL], Take a look at the ALTITUDE GAUGE, when it displays 500 Feet from ground, once again go to [V]IEW SELECTOR, hit [CENTER PEDESTAL], then press [LDG ATT].
Press [LDG ATT] NOW![CENTER PEDESTAL].
Your vertical velocity should be decreasing by now.
Now Jettison the Parachutes, [V]IEW SELECTOR, hit [CENTER PEDESTAL] [PARA JETT].
Congratulations, you just landed safely!

Title: Tutorial 8 - Deorbit, Entry & Landing
